/*!
 * @brief     Lattice FPGA / Raspberry Pi 5 platform configuration and control.
 *
 *            The Raspberry Pi 5 is the SPI host. A Lattice FPGA proxies SPI0 to
 *            the JESD IP register interface (CS0) and to the AD9986 (CS1); SPI1
 *            reaches the HMC7044 clock generator.
 *
 *            SPI device mapping:
 *               - SPI0 CS0 (/dev/spidev0.0) : JESD IP register interface
 *               - SPI0 CS1 (/dev/spidev0.1) : AD9986
 *               - SPI1 CS0 (/dev/spidev1.0) : HMC7044
 *
 *            The JESD IP register interface is re-routed over SPI0 CS0 by
 *            re-implementing ads9_axi_reg_read32()/ads9_axi_reg_write32(), so
 *            the existing adi_ads9_* JESD configuration API is reused unchanged.
 *
 *            This platform implements the SPI control/configuration plane only.
 *            JESD204 DMA data capture (the Xilinx CDMA path) is not supported;
 *            the cdma_* entry points are provided as unsupported stubs so the
 *            adi_ads9 module links without the Xilinx DMA stack.
 *
 * @copyright copyright(c) 2024 analog devices, inc. all rights reserved.
 *            This software is proprietary to Analog Devices, Inc. and its
 *            licensor. By using this software you agree to the terms of the
 *            associated analog devices software license agreement.
 */

